'''Arcillera''' is a small village in the [[province of Zamora]], Spain, close to the border with [[Portugal]].
A [[Celts|Celtic]] hoard of silver jewellery and [[denarii]] dating to approximately 20 BC was found in Arcillera in the early twentieth century. It is now mostly preserved in the collections of the [[British Museum]].<ref>[https://www.britishmuseum.org/research/collection_online/search.aspx?place=4791&plaA=4791-3-1 British Museum Collection]</ref>
