{{Infobox book |name = K.G. Subramanyan, a Retrospective |title_orig = |translator = |image = K.G. Subramanyan, a Retrospective.jpg |caption = |author = [[R. Siva Kumar]] |illustrator = |cover_artist = |country = [[India]] |language = English |series = |subject = Art |genre = |publisher = [[National Gallery of Modern Art]] |pub_date = February 16, 2010 |english_pub_date = |pages = 224 pages |isbn = 8187902132 |oclc = |preceded_by = |followed_by = }}
'''''K.G. Subramanyan, a Retrospective''''' is a book by [[R. Siva Kumar]], released on the occasion of the fourth and largest retrospective show of [[K.G. Subramanyan]], which was curated by [[R. Siva Kumar]] at the [[National Gallery of Modern Art]].<ref>https://books.google.com/books/about/K_G_Subramanyan_a_Retrospective.html?id=HcefAAAAMAAJ</ref>
The exhibition consisted of 300 paintings including terracotta reliefs, reverse paintings on glass and acrylic, linocuts, lithographs, etching, silkscreens,<ref>http://www.frontline.in/static/html/fl2009/stories/20030509000807900.htm</ref> drawings, studies, children's books, toys and saras-paintings on terracotta platters-and the photographs of murals. and the range of materials includes terracotta, glass, paper, wood porcelain and metal cement.<ref>http://www.thehindu.com/thehindu/mag/2003/03/02/stories/2003030200130200.htm</ref>
The book offers an insight into the creative processes of [[K.G. Subramanyan]]. While tracing the various aspects of his creativity, the book provides the influences that shaped him and gives a kaleidoscopic view of his six-decade long artistic journey from [[Kerala]], [[Mahé, India|Mahe]], [[Santiniketan]], [[Slade School]] in [[England]], and later in various cities of [[Europe]] and [[United States|America]].<ref>http://www.saffronart.com/sitepages/ArticleDetails.aspx?Articleid=146</ref>
This book features as a part of the syllabus of Modern South Asian art at various universities.<ref>http://www.vam.ac.uk/content/articles/m/reading-list-modern-south-asian-art/</ref>
